Media Mix Modeling data request
This article walks you through the steps to access Media Mix Modeling data through API.

Introduction
Media Mix Modeling (MMM) is a measurement technique that leverages time-series modeling to understand the business impacts (prices) of all traditional and digital marketing touchpoints. By accounting for operations such as pricing, external factors, and economic factors, MMM can quantify ROI across an advertiser’s media channels and provide insight to future media spend planning.

You can use MMM API to access MMM data and this helps you streamline your MMM data request experience, and elevate operational efficiency and scalability.

Prerequisites
You've gained access to TikTok API for Business. See Get Started - Step by step workflow for details. Ensure that you complete Marketing API authorization and authentication.
To create Traffic ads, you need relevant permissions. See API Reference to find out permissions required for endpoints (including the endpoints listed in the "Steps" section) and see Update app permissions to find out how to configure permissions.
Ensure that your developer app has the permission scope MMM Data Report under Reporting.
Accessing MMM data through API requires setting up ad accounts in Business Center first.
Add the ad accounts to the Business Center. You can either create ad accounts in a Business Center using /bc/advertiser/create/ or request access to ad accounts in Business Center.
Ensure that you have access to the ad accounts that you want to use to access MMM data for. To do this, call /bc/asset/get/ and set asset_type to ADVERTISER.
If the returned advertiser_role for the ad account is not ADMIN, OPERATOR, or ANALYST, you don't have access to these ad accounts. Ask one admin for the Business Center to share the ad accounts with you and grant access using /bc/asset/assign/. The Business Center admin needs to specify asset_type as ADVERTISER and advertiser_role as ADMIN, OPERATOR, or ANALYST.
Steps
Create an MMM data request using /mmm/api/create/.
Example

Request

curl --location --request POST 'https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/mmm/api/create/' \
--header 'Access-Token: {{Access-Token}}'
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '{
    "advertiser_ids": [
        "{{advertiser_id}}"
    ],
    "request_info": {
        "targets": [
            {
                "advertiser_id": "{{advertiser_id}}"
            }
        ],
        "from_date": "2024-01-01",
        "to_date": "2024-01-03",
        "country_code": [
            "JP","US","CA"
        ],
        "media_type": "All"
    },
    "email": "{{email}}"
}'
Response

HTTPS/1.1 200 OK
{
    "code": 0,
    "message": "OK",
    "request_id": "{{request_id}}",
    "data": {
        "mmm_request_id": "{{mmm_request_id}}"
    }
}
Check the data request status using /mmm/api/check/.
